{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6d3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s932"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"932"},"text":"§ 932.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Art. 132. Retaliation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6d4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s932/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In General","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Any person subject to this chapter who, with the intent to retaliate against any person for reporting or planning to report a criminal offense, or making or planning to make a protected communication, or with the intent to discourage any person from reporting a criminal offense or making or planning to make a protected communication—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6d5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s932/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" wrongfully takes or threatens to take an adverse personnel action against any person; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6d6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s932/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" wrongfully withholds or threatens to withhold a favorable personnel action with respect to any person;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"shall be punished as a court-martial may direct.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6d7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s932/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this section:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6d8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s932/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “protected communication” means the following:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6d9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s932/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A lawful communication to a Member of Congress or an Inspector General.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6da-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s932/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" A communication to a covered individual or organization in which a member of the armed forces complains of, or discloses information that the member reasonably believes constitutes evidence of, any of the following:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6db-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s932/b/1/B/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A violation of law or regulation, including a law or regulation prohibiting sexual harassment or unlawful discrimination.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6dc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s932/b/1/B/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Gross mismanagement, a gross waste of funds, an abuse of authority, or a substantial and specific danger to public health or safety.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6dd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s932/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “Inspector General” has the meaning given that term in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1034/j"},"text":"section 1034(j) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6de-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s932/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “covered individual or organization” means any recipient of a communication specified in clauses (i) through (v) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1034/b/1/B"},"text":"section 1034(b)(1)(B) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6df-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s932/b/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “unlawful discrimination” means discrimination on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, or national origin.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida82fc6e0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/328/dE/tLX/s5450"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–328, div. E, title LX, § 5450","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/2957"},"text":"130 Stat. 2957","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/91/dA/tX/s1081/c/1/Q"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–91, div. A, title X, § 1081(c)(1)(Q)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 2017","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/131/1599"},"text":"131 Stat. 1599","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida82fc6e1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida82fc6e2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"ida82fc6e3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 932 was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s924"},"text":"section 924 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida82fc6e4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2017—Subsec. (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/91"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–91","children":[],"tail":" substituted “section 1034(j)” for “section 1034(h)”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"ida82fc6e5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"ida82fc6e6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2017 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/91"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–91","children":[],"tail":" effective immediately after the amendments made by div. E (§§ 5001–5542) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/328"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–328","children":[],"tail":" take effect as provided for in section 5542 of that Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s801"},"text":"10 U.S.C. 801","children":[],"tail":" note), see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/91/s1081/c/4"},"text":"section 1081(c)(4) of Pub. L. 115–91","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s801"},"text":"section 801 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"ida82fc6e7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2019","children":[],"tail":", as designated by the President, with implementing regulations and provisions relating to applicability to various situations, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/328/s5542"},"text":"section 5542 of Pub. L. 114–328","children":[],"tail":" and Ex. Ord. No. 13825, set out as notes under "},{"ta